Name :gg_linefighter. ______________ Ok, black and white gungame or can be used for knife game (whatever u feel like) because no buy zone. Multiple ways to commence battle. A tower with a sniper spot for those hard scout and awp levels. Underground provides instant action. A SECRET AREA great for escaping a player on knife level providing you know where it is. Plenty of space for heavy amounts of players. The black and white stripes are obviously ladders if you couldn't tell. Yes it is fullbright i tried adding even a lot of light and env light, the reason for this is because when you add lights it makes considerably darker making it nearly impossible to see black on black. fullbright provides just the right amount of light. Enjoy, please leave a comment or thoughts. _______________ GL&HF

GG_LEMONADE by [OcUK]_Sniff 
I began this project back when I played DoD:S and I never really finished it. The map was fine and playable, but it was orange dev themed, and it still needed tweaks. When CS:S caught my attention I re-opened the project and set about porting it across and improving it.

When creating this map I considered gameplay balance as paramount. I took the easy road and made it symmetrical to start off, and then planned out the level on paper several times before even going into Hammer. The key focus to this level is to make it feel enclosed, but always providing more than one option of where to go next. Not only that, but also to keep the gameplay three dimensional. This isn't a forwards and backwards map, I've made sure to create lots of high ground and low ground throughout to provide this 3D experience.

Finally, the texturing which was originally orange became what it is now.  A mix of hard concrete blocks, white brick walls, tiled floor and all brought together by yellow neon embelishments. Not the best ever, but it seems to fit. The concrete definately emphasises the WW2-like bunkers in the level.

Includes:
32 spawns
Balanced symmetrical layout
Working radar
Working nav mesh
Custom textures

Please rate and assess.

Enjoy!

This is my first map. After reading some tutorials 4 days ago, I decided to get my feet wet.

Special thanks to mck-76...the original mapper of gg_lego_arena (proper credits are given in the txt file and on a textured map decal visible on the map).

The modifications include:
1. Expanded the walkable surface
2. The 4 blocks located in corners are now rooms
3. Added tunnels in the lower level that can access the 4 rooms
4. Retextured the brushes.

The black and white textures were intentionally used to depict a mafia colorization for my clan.

Please give some feedback and be critical. I know that I have a long ways to go to be a mapper.

The zip files includes the bsp, nav, txt, and gg spawnpoints.
